ANTHRAX - ARMENIA (04): (ARMAVIR) CATTLE, OIE
*********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Mon 2 Sep 2019
Source: OIE, WAHIS (World Animal Health Information System), weekly disease information 2019; 32(36) [edited]
https://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=31632


Anthrax, Armenia
----------------
Information received on [and dated] 2 Sep 2019 from Dr Georgi Avetisyan, head, Food Safety Inspection Body of the Government of the Republic of Armenia, e ARM Ministry of Agriculture of the Republic of Armenia, Yerevan, Armenia

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 29 Aug 2019
Date of confirmation of the event: 30 Aug 2019
Reason for notification: recurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 30 Dec 2012
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: _Bacillus anthracis_
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (basic)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak location: Getashen, Getashen, Armavir, Armavir
Date of start of the outbreak: 29 Aug 2019
Outbreak status: resolved (30 Aug 2019)
Epidemiological unit: village
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Cattle / 10 / 1 / 1 / 0 / 0
Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 10 / 10 / 100 / 10
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive, contact with wild species

Control measures
Measures applied: surveillance within containment and/or protection zone; screening; official disposal of carcasses, by-products, and waste; vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists); no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: Republican Veterinary-Sanitary and Phytosanitary Laboratory Services Center (national laboratory)
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Cattle / Ascoli test / 30 Aug 2019 / positive
Cattle / bacteriological examination / 30 Aug 2019 / positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

